thanks @becketqin @ijuma 
    **1.** I have tried to optimize code like below, add a new super class and method as below.
"trait ControllerZkChildListener extends IZkChildListener {
  @throws(classOf[Exception])
  def handleChildChange(parentPath : String, curChilds : java.util.List[String]): Unit = {
    //to do controller is active check
    doHandleChildChange(parentPath, curChilds)
  }

  @throws(classOf[Exception])
  def doHandleChildChange(parentPath : String, currentBrokerList : java.util.List[String])
}"
    **2.** Take TopicChangeListener as an example. we define TopicChangeListener like "class TopicChangeListener extends ControllerZkChildListener with Logging" and redefine doHandleChildChange method in this subclass. we should define doHandleChildChange in every subclass that extends from ControllerZkChildListener.
    **3.** But the trouble is we should get KafkaController instance in our super class to judge it isActive() before we call doHandleChildChange.so we should implement a singleton get method in object KafkaController. and we also should declare class KafkaController as private.  and the construction of KafkaController should declare like "kafkaController = new KafkaController(config, zkUtils, brokerState, kafkaMetricsTime, metrics, threadNamePrefix)"
    **4.** The advantage of this scala aop decrease the repeated check logic in the subclass, but it also add modifies as above，I wonder whether we need to make this change now.
    cc @ijuma @becketqin
